      "message": "OK, there are actually three CLs to review, this is the last of the three. I tried to break it up so that the earlier ones are simpler, but they don\u0027t make much sense until this CL (which is the big payoff).\n\n- The first CL is largely mechanical, adding the idea of shared program elements.\n- The second CL uses that in a very simple way, to change how shared variable declarations are handled.\n- This CL moves shared functions to the new world, which opened a can of worms. As a result, it has a bunch of changes that spiral out from there. I can try to split this one up a bit, if that helps? Some of the ir generator and inliner refactoring could be done standalone.",
      "revId": "ff6f81c8f7c2bcb2c45f1558fbfad358ff16a7e2",
