      "writtenOn": "2020-11-19T17:19:14Z",
      "side": 1,
      "message": "Moving this here (vs. convertProgram) ensures that:\n1) It\u0027s only done once.\n2) It\u0027s done *before* we try to load/optimize the GPU module at run-time. Otherwise we end up optimizing the GPU blend functions with an empty caps map.\n\nOnce I stumbled on to that issue, I figured it made sense to hoist the initialization of caps and context in the inliner, too - those are things that are tied to the compiler, and can\u0027t change per-program.",
      "revId": "ff6f81c8f7c2bcb2c45f1558fbfad358ff16a7e2",
      "serverId": "5086850b-e599-37d2-8ec8-ff16aeccbf02"
